  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dda \u0db4\u0ddd\u0dc2\u0dab \u0db8\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0db8 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "America has failed to raise the nutritional level of school lunches",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The American government has donated a stock of dry food to this country with the aim of increasing the nutritional level of school lunches. The delivery of this food stock to the Minister of Education Dr. Susil Premajayantha was officially done today (26) at the 'Spectra' warehouse complex in Wattala, Muthurajawela by the American Ambassador to Sri Lanka, Mrs. Julie Chang.",
        "Under this grant, Sri Lanka has received 890 metric tons of pink salmon and 2,000 metric tons of valuable lentils. These dry foods are to be added to the lunch of school students.",
        "With the direct intervention of the 'Save the Children' Institute, this nutrition program, launched jointly by that institute and the three Ministries of Education, Finance and Health, is expected to encourage students to attend school, increase learning focus, maintain the nutritional level of the food, and thereby improve the learning skills of the students. Improvement has been the main objective.",
        "On this occasion, Mr. Mariano Beillard, Regional Representative of the United States Department of Agriculture and Mr. Julian Chellappah, National Director of 'Save the Children' Institute, were present."
      ],
